As NexusAI, I'll create a portfolio website for a professional photographer with a clean, modern design.

Here's the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code for the website:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Photography Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#gallery">Gallery</a></li>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <!-- Home Page -->
        <section id="home">
            <h1>Photography Portfolio</h1>
            <p>Welcome to my photography portfolio! I'm a professional photographer with a passion for capturing life's moments.</p>
            <button onclick="showGallery()">View My Work</button>
        </section>

        <!-- Gallery -->
        <section id="gallery">
            <h2>Gallery:</h2>
            <ul id="gallery-list"></ul>
        </section>

        <!-- About Page -->
        <section id="about">
            <h2>About:</h2>
            <p>I'm a professional photographer with years of experience in capturing life's moments. From weddings to portraits, I've got you covered.</p>
            <img src="profile-pic.jpg" alt="Profile Picture">
        </section>

        <!-- Contact Form -->
        <section id="contact">
            <h2>Contact:</h2>
            <form id="contact-form">
                <label for="name">Name:</label>
                <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
                <label for="email">Email:</label>
                <input type="email" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
                <label for="message">Message:</label>
                <textarea id="message" name="message"></textarea><br><br>
                <button type="submit">Send</button>
            </form>
        </section>
    </main>

    <!-- JavaScript -->
    <script>
        function showGallery() {
            const galleryList = document.getElementById('gallery-list');
            // Load the gallery images from a JSON file or API
            const galleryData = [
                { title: 'Wedding', image: 'image1.jpg' },
                { title: 'Portrait', image: 'image2.jpg' },
                { title: 'Landscape', image: 'image3.jpg' }
            ];

            galleryList.innerHTML = '';
            for (const image of galleryData) {
                const listItem = document.createElement('li');
                listItem.innerHTML = `<img src="${image.image}" alt="${image.title}">`;
                galleryList.appendChild(listItem);
            }
        }
    </script>

    <!-- Styles -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, .1);
        }

        nav ul {
            list-style: none;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
        }

        nav li {
            margin-right: 20px;
        }

        main {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, .1);
        }

        section {
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        #gallery-list {
            list-style: none;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        #gallery-list li {
            display: inline-block;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a basic portfolio website with a home page, gallery, about page, and contact form. The gallery section displays a list of images with titles, and the about page shows a profile picture.

To use this code, you'll need to:

1. Create a new folder for your project and add the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files.
2. Replace the `profile-pic.jpg` image with your own profile picture.
3. Load the gallery images from a JSON file or API using the `galleryData` variable in the JavaScript code.
4. Update the contact form's action attribute to point to your preferred contact handling script.

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any questions or need further assistance.

